                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.119/24551): Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-13T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 13, 1918—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3527. For Sheldon [from War Trade Board]: No. 1831. Please keep us fully informed
                    as to any proposals with regard to the resumption of trade with enemy territory
                    now occupied by the military forces of the Allies, particularly
                    Alsace-Lorraine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
